'''歐亞航空公司'''（Eurasia Aviation Corporation）是一个[[中華民國大陸時期|中國]]已結業航空公司，总部在[[上海市_(中華民國)|上海]]，<ref>''{{link-en|Flight International|Flight International}}''. April 28, 1938. p. [http://www.flightglobal.com/pdfarchive/view/1938/1938%20-%201198.html?search=Eurasia 416] {{Wayback|url=http://www.flightglobal.com/pdfarchive/view/1938/1938%20-%201198.html?search=Eurasia |date=20141006084148 }} ([https://www.webcitation.org/6T5QG4M9B?url=http://www.flightglobal.com/FlightPDFArchive/1938/1938%20-%201198.PDF Archive]). " EURASIA AVIATION CORP., 97, Jinkee Road, Shanghai."</ref>为一家中国和德国合营的企业。<ref>"[http://www.chinastampsociety.org/stamp-and-auction-catalogs/eurasia-aviation-corporation-a-german-chinese-airline-in-china-and-its-airmail-1931-1943-by-peter-moeller-and-larry-d-sall-paperback-in-color-2007-153-pages-great-book-on-the-history-of-this-airline-includes-a-listing-of-first-flight-covers-and-catalog-values/item-28 Eurasia Aviation Corporation - A German-Chinese Airline in China and its Airmail 1931-1943 by Peter Moeller and Larry D. Sall, paperback in color, 2007, 153 pages, great book on the history of this airline, includes a listing of First Flight covers and catalog values] {{Wayback|url=http://www.chinastampsociety.org/stamp-and-auction-catalogs/eurasia-aviation-corporation-a-german-chinese-airline-in-china-and-its-airmail-1931-1943-by-peter-moeller-and-larry-d-sall-paperback-in-color-2007-153-pages-great-book-on-the-history-of-this-airline-includes-a-listing-of-first-flight-covers-and-catalog-values/item-28 |date=20141006121204 }}." China Stamp Society. Retrieved on October 4, 2014.</ref>1931年2月<ref>{{cite book |title=上海通志 |chapterurl=http://www.shtong.gov.cn/dfz_web/DFZ/Info?idnode=79579&tableName=userobject1a&id=104043 |chapter=第二十九卷交通运输下/第三章航空运输/第三节 航线 |quote=1931年2月，中德合办欧亚航空公司成立 |access-date=2019-01-06 |archive-date=2019-01-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190106155159/http://www.shtong.gov.cn/dfz_web/DFZ/Info?idnode=79579&tableName=userobject1a&id=104043 |dead-url=no }}</ref>由中华民国国民政府交通部和{{link-en|德意志汉莎航空|Deutsche Luft Hansa}}[[中德合作|合作]]成立<ref>{{cite book |editor=民航华东地区史志编纂办公室 |title=上海民用航空志 |publisher=上海社会科学院出版社 |isbn=7806187405 |chapterurl=http://www.shtong.gov.cn/dfz_web/DFZ/Info?idnode=68531&tableName=userobject1a&id=66065 |chapter=附录：中华民国国民政府交通部与德国汉莎航空公司订立欧亚航空邮运合同 |access-date=2019-01-06 |archive-date=2019-01-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190106153428/http://www.shtong.gov.cn/dfz_web/DFZ/Info?idnode=68531&tableName=userobject1a&id=66065 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

[[中華民國交通部|中華民國交通部]]将歐亞航空定为国有<ref name=BallantineTangp6>Ballantine, Collin and Pamela Tang. "Chinese airlines: airline colours of China." [[Airlife|Airlife]], 1995. p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=cgAKAQAAMAAJ&q=Eurasia+airlines+China&dq=Eurasia+airlines+China&hl=en&output=html_text&sa=X&ei=1EswVMmbDdiBygSpjYEI&ved=0CDkQ6AEwAw 6].  "Chinese Ministry of Communications which declared Eurasia to be a Chinese State-owned airline. The airline then fell into more trouble as a direct result of the continuing Japanese occupation. The fleet of airliners was based in Hong Kong[...]"</ref> 使用{{link-en|容克斯W33|Junkers W33}}作为主要机型。<ref>Ballantine, Collin and Pamela Tang. "Chinese airlines: airline colours of China." [[Airlife|Airlife]], 1995. p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=cgAKAQAAMAAJ&q=Eurasia+airlines+China&dq=Eurasia+airlines+China&hl=en&output=html_text&sa=X&ei=1EswVMmbDdiBygSpjYEI&ved=0CDkQ6AEwAw 5]. "The outcome of this venture was Eurasia Airlines, operating six- seater Junkers W33 airliners across Asia into China."</ref> ，也有使用10架[[Ju_52運輸機|Ju 52]]。

歐亞航空和[[中國航空|中國航空]]（中美合資）為[[抗日戰爭|中日戰爭]]前中國兩大航空公司，飛行員都是德國人，[[空中服務員|空中服務員]]早期也是歐美女性，後來才有中國女性加入。
